text: Valley County is a county in the U.S. state of Idaho. As of the 2020 census, 11,746 people lived there. The county seat is Cascade, and the largest city is McCall. == Communities == === Cities === * Cascade * Donnelly * McCall === Census-designated places === * Smiths Ferry * Yellow Pine === Other unincorporated communities === * Big Creek * Lake Fork * Roseberry * Warm Lake == References == Category:Idaho counties Category:1910s establishments in Idaho Category:1917 establishments in the United States
title: Valley County, Idaho
